Composition and appointment. The governing body of the Commission shall be a board of directors that consists of twelve (12) voting members from the following organizations and any additional members selected by the Executive Committee pursuant to (c) below:


The County Manager, Deputy County Manager, or Assistant County Manager;



The Director of the Miami-Dade Parks Department;



A representative from the Miami-Dade League of Cities;



A representative who is involved in collegiate athletics from one of the local colleges or universities to be selected by the board of directors;



A representative from the Miami-Dade School Board;



A representative from the Greater Miami Convention and Visitors Bureau;



A representative from the Greater Miami and the Beaches Hotel Association;



A representative from The Greater Miami Chamber of Commerce;



A representative from The Orange Bowl Committee.



A member of the Board of County Commissioners to be appointed by the Chairman or Chairperson of the Board of County Commissioners;



A member of the Board of County Commissioners to be appointed by the Chairman or Chairperson of the Board of County Commissioners;



The Miami-Dade County Mayor or his designee.
Each organization shall appoint its representative to the board of directors. When making a selection, each organization shall consider that the voting members should reflect the gender, racial, ethnic or cultural make-up of the community.
